text:
It's actually more complicated than that, and even more confusing if you're not careful:

• slicing series with just `[]`is just like Numpy, i.e. upper bound excluded;
• slicing dataframes by position using `.iloc[]` is like Numpy, i.e. upper bound excluded;
• slicing dataframes by label using `.loc[]` is with upper bound _included_, even if the labels are integers (which is probably what confuses people most. You need to have a real grasp of row positions vs. row labels).
Things get hairy when you combine slicing by label with slicing by position, or include conditions or masks in the mix. Luckily I don't need to use slices often...
